Sentencas: A calcium-doped ceria (Ce1-xCaxO2-delta, 0 <= x <= 0.3) has been applied as a ceramic support in NiMo-based catalysts for an internal reforming tubular solid oxide fuel cell running on isooctane.
Titulo: NiMo-calcium-doped ceria catalysts for inert-substrate-supported tubular solid oxide fuel cells running on isooctane

Sentencas: Introducing calcium into the CeO2-based ceramic was found to improveconductivity of Ce1-xCaxO2-delta.
Titulo: NiMo-calcium-doped ceria catalysts for inert-substrate-supported tubular solid oxide fuel cells running on isooctane

Sentencas: The Ce0.9Ca0.1O2-delta (x = 0.10) sample exhibited an optimum conductivity of 0.045 S cm(-1) at 750 degrees C.
Titulo: NiMo-calcium-doped ceria catalysts for inert-substrate-supported tubular solid oxide fuel cells running on isooctane

Sentencas: The transport of oxygen ions in Ce1-xCaxO2-delta promoted the catalytic partial oxidation of isooctane in the NiMo-Ce1-xCaxO2-delta catalyst, which increased the fuel conversion as well as H-2 and CO yields.
Titulo: NiMo-calcium-doped ceria catalysts for inert-substrate-supported tubular solid oxide fuel cells running on isooctane

Sentencas: As a result, the NiMo-Ce0.9Ca0.1O2-delta (x = 0.10) catalyst exhibited a high isooctane conversion of 98%, and the H-2 and CO yields achieved 74% and 83%, respectively, for reforming of isooctane and air at the O/C ratio of 1.0 at 750 degrees
Titulo: NiMo-calcium-doped ceria catalysts for inert-substrate-supported tubular solid oxide fuel cells running on isooctane

Sentencas: C. Furthermore, the NiMo-Ce0.9Ca0.1O2-delta catalyst has been applied as an internal reforming layer for an inert-substrate-supported tubular solid oxide fuel cell running on isooctane/air.
Titulo: NiMo-calcium-doped ceria catalysts for inert-substrate-supported tubular solid oxide fuel cells running on isooctane

Sentencas: Due to its high reforming activity, the single cell presented an initial maximum power density of 355 mW cm(-2) in isooctane/air at 750 degrees C and displayed stable electrochemical performance during similar to 30 h operation.
Titulo: NiMo-calcium-doped ceria catalysts for inert-substrate-supported tubular solid oxide fuel cells running on isooctane

Sentencas: These results demonstrated the application feasibility of the NiMo-Ce0.9Ca0.1O2-delta catalyst for direct internal reforming solid oxide fuel cells running on isooctane/air.
Titulo: NiMo-calcium-doped ceria catalysts for inert-substrate-supported tubular solid oxide fuel cells running on isooctane
